    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Knotted pile weaving suspended in a doorway from a rod about 10 inches above the threshold in order to keep out dust and animals; rug is up to 12 inches long by 35 inches wide.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000040671/Mackie and Thompson, Turkmen (1980)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tejido de pelo anudado colgado en el umbral de una puerta de entrada de una barra de aproximadamente 10 pulgadas que sirve para mantener fuera el polvo y los animales; la alfombra tiene más de 12 pulgadas de largo por 35 pulgadas de ancho.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Geknoopte poolweefsels, opgehangen aan een stok in een deuropening ongeveer 25 cm boven de drempel om stof en dieren buiten te houden circa 30 cm lang en 90 cm breed.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>打結的絨毛編織物，由棍子懸掛在門檻上方約10英吋處，避免灰塵飛入或小動物闖入。約12英吋長，35英吋寬。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Geknüpftes Flor-Gewebe, das von einer Stange 10 Inches (ca. 25 cm) oberhalb der Schwelle im Türrahmen herunterhängt, um Staub und Tier herauszuhalten; der Teppich ist bis zu 12 Inches (ca. 30 cm) lang und 35 Inches (ca. 90 cm) breit.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
